Note:
This file handles interference graph construction and register interference analysis.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process interference graph construction and register interference analysis
- Handle interference detection and interference graph optimization
- Manage interference-based register allocation and interference validation
- Process interference verification and interference analysis

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Interference graph construction enables graph coloring register allocation
- Proper interference analysis ensures correct register conflict detection
- Interference analysis support enables Runa compilation for optimized register allocation

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Adjacency-list interference graph backed by collections/ordered_map
- Backward per-instruction interference construction from liveness results
- Graph statistics, coalescing tests, verification, and debug printing

Representation notes (task #473):
- The graph maps register id -> neighbor List. Register ids are INTEGERS, so
  the map is an OrderedMap: the previous Dictionary representation
  string-hashed its keys (each integer key was dereferenced as a string
  pointer) and crashed at runtime.
- Liveness register sets (block live_in/live_out and the per-instruction
  def/use sets) are OrderedMaps enumerated with the omap_first /
  omap_entry_next entry walk - never with Dictionary key Lists.
- Instruction def/use extraction is delegated to liveness.runa
  (get_instruction_defs / get_instruction_uses), which resolves the
  dual-shape instruction records through LIR.lir_resolve_instruction_base
  and models call/syscall/div/shift clobbers. This file never reads
  instruction operand slots directly.

Dependencies:
- Requires liveness.runa for live-out sets and def/use extraction
- Imports LIR types for function and block structures
- Imports memory/layout.runa for OWNED HEAP allocation (Tier 3)
- Imports collections/ordered_map and collections/list for graph storage
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/lir/lir.runa" as LIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/lir/liveness.runa" as Liveness
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as MemoryCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/ordered_map.runa" as OrderedMap
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Interference Graph Construction
Note: ============================================================================

Note:
OVERVIEW:
---------
This file builds an interference graph from liveness analysis results.
Two registers interfere if one is DEFINED at a program point where the
other is LIVE (i.e., their live ranges overlap). The def-against-live
formulation also captures dead definitions: a value that is never used
still occupies a register at its definition point and must not clobber
values that live across that instruction.

The interference graph is used by register allocation (register_alloc.runa)
to perform graph coloring - registers that interfere cannot be assigned
the same physical register.

INTEGRATION WITH LIVENESS:
--------------------------
build_interference_graph ensures liveness itself: when the function's
blocks carry no computed live_in/live_out sets it invokes
Liveness.compute_function_liveness before constructing edges. Callers
that already ran liveness pay only a pointer test.

ALGORITHM:
----------
For each basic block B (backward, mirroring the liveness transfer function):
  current_live := live_out[B]
  For each instruction I from last to first:
    For each def d of I:
      For each r in current_live, r != d: add edge (d, r)
      For each other def d2 of I:        add edge (d, d2)
    current_live := (current_live - defs(I)) ∪ uses(I)

The def-def edges cover multi-definition instructions (IDIV defines both
RAX and RDX; calls clobber the full caller-saved set) whose results
coexist and therefore need distinct registers.

USAGE BY REGISTER ALLOCATION:
------------------------------
Graph coloring register allocation uses this interference graph:
- Nodes with an edge cannot have the same color (physical register)
- K-coloring (K = number of physical registers available)
- If graph is not K-colorable, spilling is required
:End Note

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Interference Graph Data Structure
Note: Adjacency list: OrderedMap<register_id, List<neighbor register ids>>
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
The interference graph uses an adjacency list representation for efficient
edge queries and neighbor iteration. Each node (register) maps to a List of
all registers it interferes with.

Representation:
- graph = OrderedMap<register_id, adjacency_list> (integer keys)
- adjacency_list = List<register_id> (neighbors)
- Undirected graph: if A interferes with B, then B interferes with A

This representation supports O(1) node lookup and O(degree) neighbor
iteration, which is what graph coloring needs. OrderedMap preserves node
insertion order, so simplification scans are deterministic.
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_interference_graph" that takes nothing returns Integer:
    Let graph be proc omap_create from OrderedMap
    Return graph
End Process

@Reasoning
Destroys an interference graph created by create_interference_graph (or the
working copies register_alloc.runa makes of one). The graph OWNS its
adjacency Lists, so each List is destroyed before the map itself. This is
the destructor counterpart required for the allocator pipeline to be
leak-free across the spill/retry loop, where the graph is rebuilt after
every spill insertion.
@End Reasoning

Process called "destroy_interference_graph" that takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with graph
    While entry is not equal to 0:
        Let adjacency_list be proc omap_entry_value from OrderedMap with entry
        If adjacency_list is not equal to 0:
            proc list_destroy from List with adjacency_list
        End If
        Set entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with entry
    End While

    proc omap_destroy from OrderedMap with graph
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Adds a node (register) to the interference graph if it doesn't already exist.
Initializes an empty adjacency list for the node. Uses omap_contains rather
than omap_get for the existence test so register id 0 (RAX) - whose
adjacency pointer is always nonzero anyway - and future sentinel choices
never conflate "missing" with a stored value.
@End Reasoning

Process called "add_graph_node" that takes graph as Integer, register_id as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Display "add_graph_node: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if node already exists
    If proc omap_contains from OrderedMap with graph, register_id is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Create empty adjacency list for this node
    Let adjacency_list be proc list_create from List
    proc omap_set from OrderedMap with graph, register_id, adjacency_list

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Adds an undirected edge between two registers, indicating they interfere.
Since the graph is undirected, adds both (r1, r2) and (r2, r1) entries.
Ensures nodes exist before adding the edge. Prevents duplicate edges and
self-loops.
@End Reasoning

Process called "add_interference_edge" that takes graph as Integer, reg1 as Integer, reg2 as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Display "add_interference_edge: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Don't add self-loops
    If reg1 is equal to reg2:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Ensure both nodes exist
    proc add_graph_node with graph, reg1
    proc add_graph_node with graph, reg2

    Note: Get adjacency lists
    Let adj1 be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with graph, reg1
    Let adj2 be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with graph, reg2

    Note: Check if edge already exists (reg2 in adj1)
    Let size1 be proc list_length from List with adj1
    Let i be 0
    Let found be 0
    While i is less than size1:
        Let neighbor be proc list_get from List with adj1, i
        If neighbor is equal to reg2:
            Set found to 1
            Set i to size1
        Otherwise:
            Set i to i plus 1
        End If
    End While

    Note: Add edge if it doesn't exist
    If found is equal to 0:
        proc append from List with adj1, reg2
        proc append from List with adj2, reg1
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Checks if two registers interfere (have an edge in the graph).
Returns 1 if they interfere, 0 otherwise.
@End Reasoning

Process called "has_interference" that takes graph as Integer, reg1 as Integer, reg2 as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Self-interference doesn't make sense
    If reg1 is equal to reg2:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get adjacency list for reg1
    Let adj1 be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with graph, reg1
    If adj1 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if reg2 is in adjacency list
    Let size be proc list_length from List with adj1
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than size:
        Let neighbor be proc list_get from List with adj1, i
        If neighbor is equal to reg2:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Returns the adjacency list (list of interfering registers) for a given register.
Returns 0 if the register is not in the graph.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_neighbors" that takes graph as Integer, register_id as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Display "get_neighbors: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let adj be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with graph, register_id
    Return adj
End Process

@Reasoning
Returns the degree of a node (number of interferences).
Used by register allocation to identify low-degree nodes for simplification.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_node_degree" that takes graph as Integer, register_id as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let adj be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with graph, register_id
    If adj is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc list_length from List with adj
End Process

@Reasoning
Removes a node from the graph, also removing all edges incident to it.
Used during the graph simplification phase of register allocation. The
node's adjacency List is OWNED by the graph and is destroyed here; callers
holding a pointer from get_neighbors on the removed node must not use it
after this call.
@End Reasoning

Process called "remove_graph_node" that takes graph as Integer, register_id as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Display "remove_graph_node: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get adjacency list for node to remove
    Let adj be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with graph, register_id
    If adj is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Remove this node from all neighbors' adjacency lists
    Let size be proc list_length from List with adj
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than size:
        Let neighbor be proc list_get from List with adj, i
        Let neighbor_adj be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with graph, neighbor

        If neighbor_adj is not equal to 0:
            Note: Find and remove register_id from neighbor's list
            Let neighbor_size be proc list_length from List with neighbor_adj
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than neighbor_size:
                Let node be proc list_get from List with neighbor_adj, j
                If node is equal to register_id:
                    proc list_remove from List with neighbor_adj, j
                    Set j to neighbor_size
                Otherwise:
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End If
            End While
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Remove node from graph and release its adjacency storage
    proc omap_remove from OrderedMap with graph, register_id
    proc list_destroy from List with adj

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Interference Graph Construction from Liveness
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Builds the complete interference graph from liveness analysis results.
This is the main entry point for interference graph construction.

Algorithm (per block, backward):
1. Seed current_live from the block's live_out set; every member becomes a
   graph node so isolated live-through values still appear in the graph.
2. At each instruction, every defined register interferes with every
   register in current_live (excluding itself) AND with every other
   register defined by the same instruction (multi-def instructions such
   as IDIV or calls produce values that coexist).
3. Remove the defs from current_live, then add the uses.

Liveness is ensured on entry: if the blocks carry no computed live sets
(live_out pointer is 0), Liveness.compute_function_liveness runs first.
The def/use extraction is shared with liveness.runa so the interference
relation and the dataflow are built from the same instruction model
(dual-shape records, call/syscall/div/shift clobbers, ABI argument uses).
@End Reasoning

Process called "build_interference_graph" that takes lir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If lir_function is equal to 0:
        Display "build_interference_graph: null function"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with lir_function, 32
    Let block_count be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with lir_function, 40

    Note: Ensure liveness results exist (finalize writes nonzero set pointers
    Note: into every block, so a zero live_out marks an unanalyzed function)
    If block_count is greater than 0:
        Let first_block be proc list_get from List with blocks, 0
        If first_block is not equal to 0:
            Let first_live_out be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with first_block, 72
            If first_live_out is equal to 0:
                Let liveness_ok be proc compute_function_liveness from Liveness with lir_function
                If liveness_ok is equal to 0:
                    Display "build_interference_graph: liveness analysis failed"
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let graph be proc create_interference_graph

    Note: Process each block
    Let b be 0
    While b is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, b
        If block is not equal to 0:
            Note: Seed current_live with the block's live-out set
            Let live_out be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 72
            Let current_live be proc create_register_set from Liveness

            If live_out is not equal to 0:
                Let out_entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with live_out
                While out_entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let out_reg be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with out_entry
                    proc register_set_add from Liveness with current_live, out_reg
                    proc add_graph_node with graph, out_reg
                    Set out_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with out_entry
                End While
            End If

            Note: Process instructions in reverse order (backward analysis)
            Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 16
            Let instruction_count be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 24

            Let inst_idx be instruction_count minus 1
            While inst_idx is greater than or equal to 0:
                Let instruction be proc list_get from List with instructions, inst_idx

                Let inst_defs be proc get_instruction_defs from Liveness with lir_function, instruction
                Let inst_uses be proc get_instruction_uses from Liveness with lir_function, instruction

                Note: Each def interferes with everything currently live and
                Note: with every other def of the same instruction
                Let def_entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with inst_defs
                While def_entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let def_reg be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with def_entry
                    proc add_graph_node with graph, def_reg

                    Let live_entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with current_live
                    While live_entry is not equal to 0:
                        Let live_reg be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with live_entry
                        proc add_interference_edge with graph, def_reg, live_reg
                        Set live_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with live_entry
                    End While

                    Let other_def_entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with inst_defs
                    While other_def_entry is not equal to 0:
                        Let other_def be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with other_def_entry
                        proc add_interference_edge with graph, def_reg, other_def
                        Set other_def_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with other_def_entry
                    End While

                    Set def_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with def_entry
                End While

                Note: current_live := (current_live - defs) ∪ uses
                Set def_entry to proc omap_first from OrderedMap with inst_defs
                While def_entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let removed_def be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with def_entry
                    proc register_set_remove from Liveness with current_live, removed_def
                    Set def_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with def_entry
                End While

                Let use_entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with inst_uses
                While use_entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let use_reg be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with use_entry
                    proc register_set_add from Liveness with current_live, use_reg
                    proc add_graph_node with graph, use_reg
                    Set use_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with use_entry
                End While

                proc register_set_destroy from Liveness with inst_defs
                proc register_set_destroy from Liveness with inst_uses

                Set inst_idx to inst_idx minus 1
            End While

            proc register_set_destroy from Liveness with current_live
        End If

        Set b to b plus 1
    End While

    Return graph
End Process

@Reasoning
Alternative construction that adds interferences between all pairs of
simultaneously live registers at each program point, in addition to the
def-against-live and def-against-def edges of the primary algorithm.

The pairwise closure is redundant for programs whose every live value has a
def inside the function (the def point already pairs it against everything
overlapping), but it also covers values that are live-in without any def -
e.g. parameter registers in functions whose parameters are never copied
out - and serves as an independent cross-check for
verify_interference_graph in tests. It is O(live²) per instruction versus
O(defs × live) for the primary algorithm, so the primary remains the
production default.
@End Reasoning

Process called "build_interference_graph_pairwise" that takes lir_function as Integer returns Integer:
    If lir_function is equal to 0:
        Display "build_interference_graph_pairwise: null function"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with lir_function, 32
    Let block_count be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with lir_function, 40

    Note: Ensure liveness results exist (same gate as the primary builder)
    If block_count is greater than 0:
        Let first_block be proc list_get from List with blocks, 0
        If first_block is not equal to 0:
            Let first_live_out be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with first_block, 72
            If first_live_out is equal to 0:
                Let liveness_ok be proc compute_function_liveness from Liveness with lir_function
                If liveness_ok is equal to 0:
                    Display "build_interference_graph_pairwise: liveness analysis failed"
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let graph be proc create_interference_graph

    Let b be 0
    While b is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, b
        If block is not equal to 0:
            Let live_out be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 72
            Let current_live be proc create_register_set from Liveness

            If live_out is not equal to 0:
                Let out_entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with live_out
                While out_entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let out_reg be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with out_entry
                    proc register_set_add from Liveness with current_live, out_reg
                    proc add_graph_node with graph, out_reg
                    Set out_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with out_entry
                End While
            End If

            Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 16
            Let instruction_count be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 24

            Let inst_idx be instruction_count minus 1
            While inst_idx is greater than or equal to 0:
                Let instruction be proc list_get from List with instructions, inst_idx

                Note: Pairwise edges among ALL currently live registers
                Let pair_entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with current_live
                While pair_entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let reg1 be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with pair_entry
                    Let pair_inner be proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with pair_entry
                    While pair_inner is not equal to 0:
                        Let reg2 be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with pair_inner
                        proc add_interference_edge with graph, reg1, reg2
                        Set pair_inner to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with pair_inner
                    End While
                    Set pair_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with pair_entry
                End While

                Let inst_defs be proc get_instruction_defs from Liveness with lir_function, instruction
                Let inst_uses be proc get_instruction_uses from Liveness with lir_function, instruction

                Note: Defs interfere with the live set and each other (this
                Note: also captures dead defs, which never enter the live set)
                Let def_entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with inst_defs
                While def_entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let def_reg be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with def_entry
                    proc add_graph_node with graph, def_reg

                    Let live_entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with current_live
                    While live_entry is not equal to 0:
                        Let live_reg be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with live_entry
                        proc add_interference_edge with graph, def_reg, live_reg
                        Set live_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with live_entry
                    End While

                    Let other_def_entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with inst_defs
                    While other_def_entry is not equal to 0:
                        Let other_def be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with other_def_entry
                        proc add_interference_edge with graph, def_reg, other_def
                        Set other_def_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with other_def_entry
                    End While

                    Set def_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with def_entry
                End While

                Note: current_live := (current_live - defs) ∪ uses
                Set def_entry to proc omap_first from OrderedMap with inst_defs
                While def_entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let removed_def be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with def_entry
                    proc register_set_remove from Liveness with current_live, removed_def
                    Set def_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with def_entry
                End While

                Let use_entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with inst_uses
                While use_entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let use_reg be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with use_entry
                    proc register_set_add from Liveness with current_live, use_reg
                    proc add_graph_node with graph, use_reg
                    Set use_entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with use_entry
                End While

                proc register_set_destroy from Liveness with inst_defs
                proc register_set_destroy from Liveness with inst_uses

                Set inst_idx to inst_idx minus 1
            End While

            proc register_set_destroy from Liveness with current_live
        End If

        Set b to b plus 1
    End While

    Return graph
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Graph Analysis and Statistics
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Computes statistics about the interference graph useful for register
allocation. Returns an OrderedMap with integer keys:
  1 = node_count, 2 = edge_count, 3 = max_degree, 4 = avg_degree
The caller owns the returned map and destroys it with omap_destroy.
@End Reasoning

Process called "compute_graph_statistics" that takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Display "compute_graph_statistics: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let stats be proc omap_create from OrderedMap

    Note: Count nodes
    Let node_count be proc omap_size from OrderedMap with graph
    proc omap_set from OrderedMap with stats, 1, node_count

    Note: Count edges and find max degree
    Let max_degree be 0
    Let total_degree be 0

    Let entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with graph
    While entry is not equal to 0:
        Let adj be proc omap_entry_value from OrderedMap with entry
        Let degree be 0
        If adj is not equal to 0:
            Set degree to proc list_length from List with adj
        End If

        Set total_degree to total_degree plus degree

        If degree is greater than max_degree:
            Set max_degree to degree
        End If

        Set entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with entry
    End While

    Note: Each edge counted twice (undirected graph)
    Let edge_count be total_degree divided by 2
    proc omap_set from OrderedMap with stats, 2, edge_count
    proc omap_set from OrderedMap with stats, 3, max_degree

    Note: Compute average degree
    Let avg_degree be 0
    If node_count is greater than 0:
        Set avg_degree to total_degree divided by node_count
    End If
    proc omap_set from OrderedMap with stats, 4, avg_degree

    Return stats
End Process

@Reasoning
Finds all nodes with degree less than K (number of available colors).
These nodes can be removed during simplification without affecting colorability.

Returns a List of register IDs with degree < K. The caller owns the List.
@End Reasoning

Process called "find_low_degree_nodes" that takes graph as Integer, k as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Display "find_low_degree_nodes: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let low_degree_nodes be proc list_create from List

    Let entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with graph
    While entry is not equal to 0:
        Let reg_id be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with entry
        Let adj be proc omap_entry_value from OrderedMap with entry
        Let degree be 0
        If adj is not equal to 0:
            Set degree to proc list_length from List with adj
        End If

        If degree is less than k:
            proc append from List with low_degree_nodes, reg_id
        End If

        Set entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with entry
    End While

    Return low_degree_nodes
End Process

@Reasoning
Finds all nodes with degree > or equal to K that are potential spill candidates.
If no low-degree nodes exist, one of these must be spilled.
Returns a List of register IDs. The caller owns the List.
@End Reasoning

Process called "find_high_degree_nodes" that takes graph as Integer, k as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Display "find_high_degree_nodes: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let high_degree_nodes be proc list_create from List

    Let entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with graph
    While entry is not equal to 0:
        Let reg_id be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with entry
        Let adj be proc omap_entry_value from OrderedMap with entry
        Let degree be 0
        If adj is not equal to 0:
            Set degree to proc list_length from List with adj
        End If

        If degree is greater than or equal to k:
            proc append from List with high_degree_nodes, reg_id
        End If

        Set entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with entry
    End While

    Return high_degree_nodes
End Process

@Reasoning
Computes a lower-bound estimate of the chromatic number (minimum colors
needed) from the maximum degree: a node of degree d may need up to d+1
colors in the worst case (itself plus all distinct-colored neighbors).
The statistics map created for the computation is destroyed before
returning so the estimator is allocation-neutral.
@End Reasoning

Process called "estimate_chromatic_number" that takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let stats be proc compute_graph_statistics with graph
    If stats is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let max_degree be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with stats, 3
    proc omap_destroy from OrderedMap with stats

    Note: Chromatic number is at most max_degree + 1
    Return max_degree plus 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Graph Coalescing Support
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Checks if two nodes can be safely coalesced (merged).
Two nodes can be coalesced if:
1. They don't interfere with each other
2. The merged node's degree is still < K (Briggs' conservative coalescing)

This is used for copy coalescing optimization in register allocation.
@End Reasoning

Process called "can_coalesce" that takes graph as Integer, reg1 as Integer, reg2 as Integer, k as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Can't coalesce if they already interfere
    Let already_interferes be proc has_interference with graph, reg1, reg2
    If already_interferes is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get degrees
    Let degree1 be proc get_node_degree with graph, reg1
    Let degree2 be proc get_node_degree with graph, reg2

    Note: Briggs' conservative coalescing:
    Note: After merge, combined degree must be < K
    Note: (Neighbors union - common neighbors)
    Let combined_degree be degree1 plus degree2

    Note: Subtract common neighbors (counted twice)
    Let adj1 be proc get_neighbors with graph, reg1
    Let adj2 be proc get_neighbors with graph, reg2

    If adj1 is not equal to 0 and adj2 is not equal to 0:
        Let size1 be proc list_length from List with adj1
        Let i be 0
        Let common be 0
        While i is less than size1:
            Let neighbor be proc list_get from List with adj1, i
            Let n_interferes be proc has_interference with graph, reg2, neighbor
            If n_interferes is equal to 1:
                Set common to common plus 1
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Set combined_degree to combined_degree minus common
    End If

    If combined_degree is less than k:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Graph Verification and Debug
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Verifies the interference graph for consistency:
- Symmetry: if A interferes with B, then B interferes with A
- No self-loops: no register interferes with itself
- Every node carries a non-null adjacency list
Integer ids are rendered through StringUtils.integer_to_string because
Display on a raw Integer treats it as a string pointer.
@End Reasoning

Process called "verify_interference_graph" that takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Display "verify_interference_graph: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let errors be 0

    Let entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with graph
    While entry is not equal to 0:
        Let reg1 be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with entry
        Let adj1 be proc omap_entry_value from OrderedMap with entry

        If adj1 is equal to 0:
            Display "verify_interference_graph: null adjacency list for register:"
            Let r1_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with reg1
            Display r1_str
            Set errors to errors plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Let size1 be proc list_length from List with adj1
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than size1:
                Let reg2 be proc list_get from List with adj1, j

                Note: Check for self-loops
                If reg1 is equal to reg2:
                    Display "verify_interference_graph: self-loop detected for register:"
                    Let loop_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with reg1
                    Display loop_str
                    Set errors to errors plus 1
                End If

                Note: Check symmetry
                Let sym_interferes be proc has_interference with graph, reg2, reg1
                If sym_interferes is equal to 0:
                    Display "verify_interference_graph: asymmetric edge:"
                    Let asym1_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with reg1
                    Display asym1_str
                    Let asym2_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with reg2
                    Display asym2_str
                    Set errors to errors plus 1
                End If

                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If

        Set entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with entry
    End While

    If errors is greater than 0:
        Display "verify_interference_graph: errors found:"
        Let err_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with errors
        Display err_str
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Prints a human-readable representation of the interference graph.
Shows each register and its interfering neighbors.
@End Reasoning

Process called "print_interference_graph" that takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Display "print_interference_graph: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Display "===== Interference Graph ====="

    Let entry be proc omap_first from OrderedMap with graph
    While entry is not equal to 0:
        Let reg_id be proc omap_entry_key from OrderedMap with entry
        Let adj be proc omap_entry_value from OrderedMap with entry

        Let reg_name be proc lir_get_register_name from LIR with reg_id
        Display "node:"
        If reg_name is not equal to 0:
            Display reg_name
        End If

        If adj is not equal to 0:
            Let degree be proc list_length from List with adj
            Display "  degree:"
            Let deg_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with degree
            Display deg_str

            Let j be 0
            While j is less than degree:
                Let neighbor be proc list_get from List with adj, j
                Let neighbor_name be proc lir_get_register_name from LIR with neighbor
                If neighbor_name is not equal to 0:
                    Display neighbor_name
                End If
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If

        Set entry to proc omap_entry_next from OrderedMap with entry
    End While

    Display "=============================="

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Prints statistics about the interference graph. The statistics map is
destroyed before returning.
@End Reasoning

Process called "print_graph_statistics" that takes graph as Integer returns Integer:
    If graph is equal to 0:
        Display "print_graph_statistics: null graph"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let stats be proc compute_graph_statistics with graph
    If stats is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_count be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with stats, 1
    Let edge_count be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with stats, 2
    Let max_degree be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with stats, 3
    Let avg_degree be proc omap_get from OrderedMap with stats, 4

    Display "===== Graph Statistics ====="
    Display "Nodes:"
    Let nodes_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with node_count
    Display nodes_str
    Display "Edges:"
    Let edges_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with edge_count
    Display edges_str
    Display "Max Degree:"
    Let max_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with max_degree
    Display max_str
    Display "Avg Degree:"
    Let avg_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with avg_degree
    Display avg_str

    Let chromatic_estimate be proc estimate_chromatic_number with graph
    Display "Estimated Chromatic Number:"
    Let chrom_str be proc integer_to_string from StringUtils with chromatic_estimate
    Display chrom_str
    Display "============================"

    proc omap_destroy from OrderedMap with stats

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Usage Example and Integration
Note: ============================================================================

Note:
USAGE EXAMPLE:
--------------
To build an interference graph (liveness is ensured automatically):

    Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/lir/interference.runa" as Interference

    Let graph be proc build_interference_graph from Interference with lir_function

    If graph is equal to 0:
        Display "Interference graph construction failed"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Verify graph (optional, for debugging)
    Let valid be proc verify_interference_graph from Interference with graph

    Note: Print statistics (optional)
    proc print_graph_statistics from Interference with graph

    Note: Use graph for register allocation
    Let context be proc allocate_registers from RegisterAlloc with lir_function, graph

    Note: Release the graph when allocation (and any retry loop) is done
    proc destroy_interference_graph from Interference with graph

GRAPH QUERIES:
--------------
Once the graph is built, you can query it:

    Note: Check if two registers interfere
    Let interferes be proc has_interference from Interference with graph, reg1, reg2

    Note: Get all registers that interfere with a register
    Let neighbors be proc get_neighbors from Interference with graph, reg_id

    Note: Get degree of a register (number of interferences)
    Let degree be proc get_node_degree from Interference with graph, reg_id

    Note: Find low-degree nodes (degree < K)
    Let low_nodes be proc find_low_degree_nodes from Interference with graph, k

GRAPH MANIPULATION:
-------------------
For register allocation simplification phase:

    Note: Remove a node from the graph (destroys its adjacency List)
    proc remove_graph_node from Interference with graph, reg_id

    Note: Check if two nodes can be coalesced
    Let can_merge be proc can_coalesce from Interference with graph, reg1, reg2, k

INTEGRATION POINTS:
-------------------
This interference graph is used by:

1. register_alloc.runa: Main consumer for graph coloring
   - Copies the graph into a working OrderedMap for simplification
   - Implements Chaitin-Briggs graph coloring with optimistic spilling
   - Identifies actual spill candidates when coloring fails

2. spilling.runa: Uses graph degrees for spill cost estimation
   - High-degree nodes free more registers when spilled

COMPILATION PIPELINE:
---------------------
1. LIR construction (lir_builder.runa)
2. Liveness analysis (liveness.runa)
3. **INTERFERENCE GRAPH** (this file)
4. Register allocation (register_alloc.runa)
5. Spill code insertion (spilling.runa)
6. Backend code generation
:End Note
